formatted_address: Ctra. antigua, N-IV, 28300 Aranjuez, Madrid, Spain
name: Camping Internacional Aranjuez

reviews.text:
Camping Aranjuez is a handy stopover site for anybody travelling to southern Spain, or going in the opposite direction. It is just south of Madrid and the town - which is attractive and lively - is home to a Royal Palace.

The campsite has a swimming pool (seasonal), restaurant, bar and shop. There is also a children's playground. The toilets and showers are of a good standard. 

However, many of the camping pitches are tired and worn out. There are a lot of semi-permanent vans and structures, which are not aesthetically appealing.

Due to its proximity to the capital, it can get very busy at weekends and during holiday periods. It might not be a first choice to stay except for its strategic convenience and easy access to Aranjuez.

We had a lovely stay on this site. Reception were very helpful, nice shop and the toilet block and showers were warm with great showers and they are kept really clean. 

It can be a bit noisy at weekends as the locals come down from Madrid for a weekend away, but remember they are also on holiday and family/friends gathering at weekends is the Spanish culture. 

The only negative is not with the site but a new restaurant in town ‘Matilde’ that literally refused to serve us coffee outside one evening and barred my husband’s entrance into the bar using two bar stools. It was our 1st night having travelled up from Granada and we can only presume they did not like the look of us (A couple in there late 50’s, my husband dressed in a plain t shirt and shorts!!!!) we felt publicly humiliated and embarrassed and never went back there during our 7 night stay. So unless you have your ‘Sunday Best’ on I would avoid this restaurant/bar as they really  need some proper hospitality training especially situated in a great location and big tourist area.

A great campsite that we stayed at longer than intended.  It is a large and well organised site with a helpful and friendly reception.  The facilities are a bit dated but, providing you search out the right block, they are toasty warm in cool weather and have good hot continuous showers and are kept clean.  The site has a restaurant and a supermarket that had fresh bread every morning.  The lovely town of Aranjuez is about 1.5 km away and you walk through the palace gardens from the footbridge.  The railway station is about 30 minutes walk away and trains go to Madrid regularly.
Stopped here for a few nights on our way to the ferry, the campsite has everything you need and more.  It is worth visiting the town it's rich in history and has some spectacular buildings
Lovely campsite, friendly staff and clean facilities. We used it mainly as a base to explore Madrid. Approx 3.5km to train station, €10 in taxi.
